post_text:
We are very excited to welcome the newest member to the Winston County Board of Education, Miss Morgan Smothers, Payroll Specialist.
“My name is Morgan Smothers and I am the new Payroll Specialist at the Central Office. I graduated from The University of Alabama in May 2018 with a Bachelor’s degree in Finance and a Bachelor’s degree in General Human Environmental Sciences. I also have a minor in Computing Technology and Applications. I am excited to serve the Winston County School System."

Making dreams come true!
We are so thankful for the opportunity to serve our community and schools. Our Special Education Coordinator, Lauren Archer, along with SP Ed teacher, Abbey Meigs, both
worked hard to make this project possible. Due to this hard work and dedication, the RISE Center at Addison Elementary was created! The Winston County School System provides our students with the best possible educational opportunities to help each one reach their full potential! We would like to thank everyone who helped with this endeavor for our school system!
#RISECenter #SpEd #dreams

shared_text:
Meek Elementary School
August 15 at 12:27 PM ·

IMPORTANT UPDATES FOR BUS RIDERS! Please Share!

Due to Covid-19 precautions, Winston Co Schools buses are limited to regular route riders only. Parents are not allowed to send notes for their children to ride home with other students on a bus. All seats will be pre-assigned with families sitting together if possible and seating charts made for contact tracing should a child become sick. Masks must be worn at all times on the bus, and no food or drink (including water) will be allowed on the bus. Also, please note that most routes will be approximately 20 minutes later than last year due to buses not arriving to school until 7:35 am.

Please share this information with your child as we prepare for the new school year. We truly appreciate your cooperation and understanding as we strive to meet guidelines.

August 10 at 5:50 PM ·

DSMS Yearbooks are here! We will have a drive-thru pick-up Monday, August 17 at 6 pm in front of the middle school. You MUST stay in your car and someone will come to your passenger side window to mark off your name and hand you your book/books. If you need to purchase a book you MUST have correct change or a check made out to DSMS. The cost is $40. If you can’t pick-up or purchase this night, they will be available on the first day of school.

post_text:
Today, State Superintendent Eric Mackey announced that students will not return to school for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year.

Winston County Schools will continue to follow the directives of the Alabama Department of Public Health and the Alabama State Department of Education.

The state department of education has promised to provide more directives for local schools in the coming days. As we know more information, we will share it with you.

We understand that these are new and uncertain times. We promise to do everything we can to continue to support the educational needs of the students of Winston County.

post_text:
FREE MEALS FOR CHILDREN UP TO AGE 18.
Beginning Monday March 30, Winston County Schools will serve all children 18 and under a supper and 5 breakfasts to carryover to the next week. Children must be in the car when picking up meals. Meals will be served from 4-6 pm.
Schedule:
Monday at WCHS. Tuesday at Addison. Wednesday at Lynn. Thursday at Double Springs Elementary. Friday at Meek.
Additional info: Children can come to all sites regardless of where they are enrolled. Meals will continue as long as there is a need. Please share this information to get the word out.

post_text: All Winston County Schools will be closed beginning Tuesday, March 17 through Friday, April 3. Employees will report to work as usual on Tuesday, March 17 to sanitize classrooms, etc., and may return to finish any remaining duties on Wednesday, March 18. Employees will be paid on Wednesday, March 18 instead of Friday, March 20. Employees not on direct deposit may pick up their check between 8 am and 3:45 pm on Wednesday. All checks not picked up will be mailed Wednesday afternoon.
